description:
Three time Eisner award winner Brian Michael Bendis (Ultimate Spider-man, Daredevil, Powers, Alias, Fortune and Glory) didn't just appear out of thin air, you know! He worked his tuchas off on all aspects of the medium before totally losing his hair in mainstream comics.

Complied in this exclusive collection are dozens of short stories, handpicked by the author, ranging from the trademark 'Fortune and Glory' style autobiographical anecdotes, to some of the darkest crime noir stories he has yet to tell.

Also included is a smattering of his favorite short work collaborations with Warren Ellis, Mike Avon Oeming, and many others. Plus a bonus portfolio of illustrations and essays that have rarely been seen before.

A fun, must have collection of very hard to find material by one of the most consistently excellent creators in modern comics.
name: Brian Michael Bendis' Total Sell Out

description: Two kid-friendly tales spooky enough for Halloween smiles from Fantagraphics Books! Stephane Blanquet's Toys in the Basement follows a hero in an embarrassing pink bunny costume as he escapes a boring Halloween party and stumbles across a secret society of toys! The Littlest Pirate King by David B. and Pierre Mac Olran, chronicles an unusual family: a crew of undead ghost pirates and the little boy they've adopted and raised as their king!
name: Ashcan

volume.name: Toys in the Basement Spook Preview

description: First Second Books celebrates Free Comic Book Day with The Train Was Bang On Time: An Episode from The Black Diamond Detective Agency by Mr. Eddie Campbell. This comic is a preview of the graphic novel First Second will publish later this spring, The Black Diamond Detective Agency, a tale of robbery, explosions, and terror in America's heartland at the turn of the twentieth century.
name: FCBD

volume.name: The Train Was Bang On Time

description: Present day. Trakk, the greatest hero our world has ever known, has been missing for decades. Modern media touts him as only ever being an urban legend, on a par with the albino alligator and Santa Claus. But he does exist and we join him at a crisis point in his long struggle. After all the years of fighting one battle after another on his quest, he only sees his failures and not the many times he has saved all humankind. Now he has all but given up. The once great hero has become a homeless drifter, a barely recognizable shadowy image of his former self. And at the time when we need him the most, he has crawled into the bottle so deep there seems no way out. Can he once again become the hero we need in time to save us all? Get ready for this one comic fans, it's monster "clobbering time!"

MISSING IN ACTION! People are disappearing in the inner city. There are rumors of unnatural creatures. The police are baffled. And our only hope is sloshed out of his freakin' gord! But meanwhile, while our hero is blitzed our villain, Vaquoul freshly regenerated is ready to wreak havoc and with his new discovery may soon be ready to make slaves of us all.
Translates Batman: The Dark Knight #13 and Nightwing #13.
